    "cultural_notes": "This salad is a modern take on a traditional ingredient. While amaranth greens (dodo) are typically cooked in Ugandan cuisine, this recipe showcases their versatility by using them raw/lightly blanched in a salad. It reflects a growing trend towards fresh, raw, and health-focused dishes in urban areas while still celebrating a beloved local green."
